race.comment: FUKUBANA (10) resumes here but the form he showed last preparation was certainly up to the mark for a race of this nature. Revved up for this with two recent trials and maps perfectly for Mallyon from gate four. Will be right there when the judge calls a halt. The well-related STREET CHASE (16) (half to 2xListed winner and G3 placed Stroll) loves this circuit with a win and two seconds from just three starts and will be high on confidence following that last-start victory. Shapes as a leading contender. ABOUT TO EXPLODE (4) has won three from four over this track and trip and is much better than the last-start performance suggests. Can bounce right back without surprising. HE'S HEAVEN (2) moderate effort last time when fourth over 1200m at Toowoomba. Include in wider plays.
